    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix LTE Turbo Rate Matching Buffer Wrap Issue\n\n### Summary\nThe `lte_rate_matching_turbo_rx` function in `lte_rate_matching.c` was not properly handling buffer wraparound when processing soft bits. This caused some soft bits to be missed during rate matching, leading to incorrect decoding results.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/lte_rate_matching.c`: Added index reset logic after first processing loop to ensure proper buffer wraparound when needed\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain conditions with specific transport block sizes and HARQ retransmissions, the function would exit the first loop with `ind == Ncb` but without resetting the index before entering the second loop. This resulted in missed soft bit processing and incorrect LLR accumulation. Observable symptoms include:\n- Higher than expected BLER in downlink reception\n- Decoding failures for specific TB sizes\n- Inconsistent HARQ combining results\n\nThe issue is most noticeable when the initial `ind` value (based on `rvidx`) is such that the first loop processes exactly to the end of the buffer, requiring a wraparound to process remaining bits.\n\n"
}